						<div class="page-head" >
							<h1>b2b商业账款催收</h1>
						</div>
						<div class="page-content" >
							<p>在生意中，有时你的客户不支付其债务，尤其是在国际贸易中。当发生这种情况，作为被欠款的一方，你面临着这样几个选择：承担损失，或者聘请那些最后也许能成功收款的律师。</p>
							
							<h2>解决方案</h2>
							<p>规避风险。找一个专业追索b2b债务的法律团队。有着各个领域专业经验的欧洲追账律师团队，从与债务人严肃沟通直至获取债务人的流动资产，bierens可以执行法庭内外的任何程序，来帮助您收回被拖欠的款项，维护您的合法权益。</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				
					<div id="page-about" class="page-container hide" >
						<div class="page-head" >
							<h1>关于我们</h1>
						</div>
						<div class="page-content" >
							<p>上海百林司律师事务所是由一群“以法维权、以法护法”为己任，拥有法学、工程学、管理学、教育学、心理学等教育背景和企业、政府工作经历的法律人发起的，以“品牌化、规模化、专业化、国际化”为发展目标，以“客户为导向，以人为本；市场本地化，服务全球化” 为服务导向，以信用管理为主要特色、涵盖公司法律、海商海事、外商投资、房地产与建筑工程、知识产权、以及刑事辩护等业务领域的综合法律服务的律师事务所。</p>
							<p>百林司是欧洲信用改革联合会（Creditreform）、美国追账局（American Bureau of Collections）指定的中国大陆地区法律及相关事务机构，同时也是荷兰Bierens 律师事务所中国地区唯一指定合作伙伴。</p>
							<p>百林司律师以提供有智慧的法律服务方案为宗旨，无论是处理诉讼业务还是非诉法律事务，均由具有深厚法学理论和丰富实践经验的资深律师承办。在处理复杂疑难的案件中，百林司律师充分发挥团队的集体智慧，多角度、全方位地深入分析案情，以百折不挠的精神，不遗余力地维护客户的合法权益，使多起看似必败的案件，转败为胜，将诉讼风险降到最低。在处理非诉讼法律业务时，百林司律师事务所充分发挥各领域专业律师的特长，以缜密的思维，优化方案，防范漏洞，使客户在商场博弈中掌握主动。</p>
							<p>以建设“精诚团结、和谐发展、协作共赢”律所文化为基础，百林司律师事务所突破了单打独斗的业务操作模式，以高度团队化、专业化的管理模式为核心竞争力，对各个法律领域的纠纷解决尤其是在信用管理的纠纷解决方面形成了自己的优势和品牌。人性化的制度管理、尽责勤勉的工作作风、创新果敢的策略思维、团结向上的精英团队，是百林司律师实现快速发展的坚强基石，是百林司律师维护客户利益的制胜法宝。</p>
							<p>百林司律师以“自强不息”为职业人生的最高境界；以“诚信至上，服务为本”为提供法律服务的行为准则。</p>
							<p>助您成功、提升价值、迈向辉煌！</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				
					<div id="page-debt-recovery" class="page-container hide" >
						<div class="page-head" >
							<h1>Maximum results on a ‘No win, No fee’ basis</h1>
							<p>Do your invoices remain unpaid? It just feels unfair. After all, you have fulfilled your side of the bargain. The last thing that you want is to incur costs to recover what is rightfully yours. We understand that as much as anyone. With the will to win, the lawyers at Bierens will do whatever is possible to ensure that as a creditor you receive justice.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="page-content" >
							<h2>Debt recovery</h2>
							
							<h3>Maximum pressure on your debtors</h3>
							<p>Are you looking for the best firm to take control of your debt recovery work? Do you want the best results? Then choose a debt recovery lawyer. Unlike a court bailiff or debt recovery agency, all conceivable tools are at a debt recovery lawyer’s disposal to put your debtors under pressure and you can confidently entrust the whole process to one safe pair of hands. With a successful outcome. Bierens Debt Recovery Lawyers have the results to prove it.</p>
							
							<h3>The most effective debt recovery process</h3>
							<p>It can take a lot of energy to recover your debts. That’s why the debt recovery lawyers of Bierens will engage all their skills and effort into ensuring that you recover the money that is rightfully yours.</p>
							
							<h3>Expertise, service and commitment</h3>
							<p>You want the firm you entrust with your debt recovery to be top class. Bierens Debt Recovery Lawyers is proof that debt recovery lawyers do not have to be remote and incomprehensible. We pride ourselves in the way we combine a strong professional approach with integrity.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				
					<div id="page-international-disputes" class="page-container hide" >
						<div class="page-head" >
							<h1>Do you have any cross-border claims or disputes? No problem!</h1>
							<p>Conducting international business attracts different kinds of problems than domestic trade. This is why we have over 30 (inter)national lawyers, as well as a large number of legal advisers, ready to assist you. They speak the language of your debtors and have a complete understanding of the laws, regulations and customs of the country in question. This is what makes Bierens your perfect partner for both national and international claims and disputes.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="page-content" >
							<h2>(Inter)national disputes</h2>
							<p>A business partner who pays late or not at all is frustrating enough, but it becomes more complicated when your debtor states he does not want to pay. What to do when your debtor claims that there is something wrong with the contract or the delivery? Disputed claims could reach the stage where legal proceedings cannot be avoided any longer. Although we always aim to prevent this, for instance by negotiating with your debtor, Bierens’ lawyers will guide you through the process if proceeding becomes necessary.</p>
							<p>As a result of a generally improved credit management, the number of the more straightforward debt recovery cases has decreased. This is good for the economy. The number of disputed claims, however, continues to grow. Disputed claims usually involve disagreements concerning business agreements and general conditions. To resolve these disputes, extensive knowledge of legislation is required.</p>
							<p>
								<span>Our (inter)national lawyers and paralegals are fully versed in the following fields of law:</span>
								<ul class="list-items" >
									<li>Contract law</li>
									<li>Insolvency law</li>
									<li>National procedural law and private law</li>
									<li>International procedural law and private law</li>
									<li>Transport law</li>
									<li>Construction law</li>
									<li>Debt collection law</li>
								</ul>
							</p>
							<p>We go the extra mile. Our lawyers assess if a dispute is valid. This allows you to continue the relationship with your business partner without delay, and for us to take steps to collect your claim successfully.</p>
							<p>Is your debtor disputing your claim or does a business partner wrongly hold you liable for a particular payment? Or has your company been summoned to appear before the Court or are you involved in a dispute concerning, for instance, rental or distribution agreements? With our broad knowledge of various areas of law, we always aim for justice, also when it comes to business disputes.</p>
							
							<h2>Expertise</h2>
							<p>Whether you have questions about certain legal procedures, or, how to draw up contracts and general terms and conditions, then our lawyers and legal advisers are on hand to advise you in simple, clear language. You can expect the same pragmatic response to any questions you may have concerning, for example, transport liability, or problems with real estate leasing. Thanks to a team of 30 lawyers and a large number of legal advisers, we have expertise in many fields of law. In the unlikely event that we are unable to answer any question, then we will be honest and tell you, since we place great emphasis on integrity. You can read a variety of interesting articles on our blog concerning different areas of law.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				
					<div id="page-advice-credit-management" class="page-container hide" >
						<div class="page-head" >
							<h1>Avoiding debt recovery and commercial disputes</h1>
							<p>Assisting you with debt recovery matters or commercial disputes is not the only way that Bierens Debt Recovery Lawyers dedicates itself to Justice for the Creditor. Preventing the need for a debt recover partner is obviously preferable.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="page-content" >
							<h2>Advice on credit management</h2>
							<p>Together we can help to minimise your risk of debt recovery matters and commercial disputes. Because prevention is better than cure, you can always come to us for advice. From SMEs to large multinationals: please contact us, without any obligation, and see what Bierens can offer you as a credit management partner.</p>
							<p>
								<span>Are your general conditions shipshape? How do you handle credit reports? In the event of a dispute, can you commence legal proceedings in your own country? We can offer, among other things:</span>
								<ul class="list-items" >
									<li>Advice on credit management and business processes</li>
									<li>A legal review of and advice on your agreements</li>
									<li>A legal review of and advice on your general conditions</li>
									<li>Advice on offers and order confirmations</li>
									<li>Evaluation of the terms of credit insurers</li>
								</ul>
							</p>
							<p>Together with your advisor your entire order-to-cash process can be optimised, from insight into your business processes to your after-sales. With a transparent policy you will not only do yourself a favour, it will also improve the relationship with your customers; it will be immediately obvious what is expected of each party. This leads to cash, gaining time in credit management and better contact with the customer. Our lawyers would be glad to advise you in order to maintain a healthy company and satisfied customers.</p>
							
							<h2>Contact</h2>
							<p>Please contact us without any obligation at <a href="mailto:info@bierensgroup.com">info@bierensgroup.com</a>, complete our contact form or contact us by telephone on <strong>021 - 55 23 92 88</strong>. We do not charge for our intial advice by telephone.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				
					<div id="page-our-philosophy" class="page-container hide" >
						<div class="page-head" >
							<h1>The most attractive debt recovery partner of choice, worldwide</h1>
							<p>Whilst debtors may feel that being in a different country keeps them safe from legal action, Bierens works on both sides of any national border. Anywhere in the world, you can rely on Bierens to provide optimum support from the best attorneys and legal advisers. With its total commitment to integrity, Bierens Debt Recovery Lawyers always focuses on achieving justice for the creditor.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="page-content" >
							<h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
							<p>The best help that anyone can give you is the right advice, and the recovery of your debt. We do everything to ensure that the debtor pays the debt owed to you, together with interest and costs. In most cases we are so successful that the additional debt recovery costs are also recovered from the debtor, provided that this is permitted by you, and by the relevant terms of your general terms and conditions. In some cases this means that it costs us more, but this is unimportant as long as our client has received justice. The debtor has paid and our client has not had to pay any costs.  Where international claims are concerned, we also do our utmost to recover costs from debtors. Wherever possible, we continue fighting till the creditor has obtained justice.</p>
